wikipedia_page.main: Alistair Fergus Murray (born 11 September 1942) is a British long-distance runner. He competed in the men's 10,000 metres at the 1964 Summer Olympics.

link_mentions.page: Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics – Men's 10,000 metres

response: He was a member of Blackheath Harriers. In 1964 he was ranked fourth in the UK behind Mike Wiggs, Fergus Murray and Bruce Tulloh.
